headline: UnitedHealth Stock Cratered on the Bad Medicare News. The Case for Buying the Dip.
summary: The health insurance business is a mess, and no health-insurance company is a bigger mess than  UnitedHealth Group  But with its shares down 17% this week, much of that mess may now be reflected in the stock price.  The bad news started on Monday, when the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, or CMS, proposed that the net price increase for Medical Advantage insurance premiums should be 0.09% in 2027, well below the 5% many had expected.  If that weren’t enough, UnitedHealth turned in less-than-stellar fourth-quarter earnings.
